paragraphs.content: The LORD reigneth, he is clothed with majesty; the LORD is clothed with strength, wherewith he hath girded himself: the world also is stablished, that it cannot be moved.
paragraphs.contentHtml: The Lord reigneth, he is clothed with majesty; the Lord is clothed with strength, wherewith he hath girded himself: the world also is stablished, that it cannot be moved.

paragraphs.content: Thy throne is established of old: thou art from everlasting.
paragraphs.contentHtml: Thy throne is established of old: thou art from everlasting.

paragraphs.content: The floods have lifted up, O LORD, the floods have lifted up their voice; the floods lift up their waves.
paragraphs.contentHtml: The floods have lifted up, O Lord, the floods have lifted up their voice; the floods lift up their waves.

paragraphs.content: The LORD on high is mightier than the noise of many waters, yea, than the mighty waves of the sea.
paragraphs.contentHtml: The Lord on high is mightier than the noise of many waters, yea, than the mighty waves of the sea.

paragraphs.content: Thy testimonies are very sure: holiness becometh thine house, O LORD, for ever.
paragraphs.contentHtml: Thy testimonies are very sure: holiness becometh thine house, O Lord, for ever.
